message: Described the use of 5G for private wireless networks, which is an important emerging trend.
Added the fact that besides smartphones and other data terminals, VoLTE capabilities are increasingly being integrated into IoT devices and wearables.
Mentioned the growing trend of private LTE networks that are being used to support existing TETRA deployments.
Added industrial applications of wearables.
Added the use of insurance services for mobile phones and consumer electronics.
Added the fact that LTE is also being used for private mobile broadband networks.
Added the expanded definition of Big Data, referring to technologies that capture, store, manage and analyze large and variable collections of data, to solve complex problems.
Added a grammatical change. A space.
Added a grammatical correct. A full stop.
Added the fact the mHealth also refers to the use of associated mobile technologies across the healthcare continuum.
Added information on the use of wearables in industries such as professional sports, retail and hospitality.

I just want to state again that, based on scientific consensus and my reasons outlined in the prior edit, that cell phone or non-ionizing electromagnetic radiation doesn't cause cancer. Suggesting it does would be very shaky and since there is already an article dedicated to this topic, it shouldn't be stated in 5G nor any other of the mobile generation articles.
